name and their ID number, the node's height and balance factor, and the objects representing the nodes to the left and right of the node
itself. As the nodes are inserted, their balance factors are calculated and if this number breaks a certain threshold, the tree is rebalanced
accordingly.
Fully functioning search as well as in-order, pre-order, and post-order printing
PageRank (C++)

November 2023

Implemented a simplified version of google's 'PageRank' algorithm.. The program takes in a specified number of string pairs as input,
with the second string representing a website that leads to another website being represented by the first string. These pairs are stored in
an adjacency list structure, with an associated pagerank that is calculated through a function once the insertion has been executed.
